article:
This is a 'list of [[districts of England]]' showing their ethnic composition as
recorded in the 2011 census.

Census Respondents were asked "What is your ethnic group? Choose ONE section
from A to E, then tick the appropriate box to indicate your cultural
background." The sections offered were:
* 'A [[White people|White]]' (Cultural backgrounds offered were: [[White
  British]]; [[Irish migration to Great Britain|White Irish]]; [[Irish
  Travellers|White Gypsy or Irish Traveller]]; [[Other White (United Kingdom
  ethnicity category)|Any other White background]])
* 'B [[British Mixed-Race|Mixed]]' (White and Black Caribbean; White and Black
  African; White and Asian; Any other Mixed background)
* 'C [[British Asian|Asian or Asian British]]' ([[British Indian|Indian]];
  [[British Pakistani|Pakistani]]; [[British Bangladeshi|Bangladeshi]];
  [[British Chinese|Chinese]]; Any other Asian background)
* 'D [[Black British|Black or Black British]]' (Caribbean; African; Any other
  Black background)
* 'E Arab or other ethnic group' ([[British Arabs|Arab]], Any other)

See also List of English districts by population - List of English
districts by area.
